frameDefinitions: An Experiencer must cope with some Condition for a prolonged period, usually against his or her will.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
An Entity survives a situation with some Support, which tends to be far below the accustomed or standard level expected.
This frame has to do with people (the Residents) residing in Locations, sometimes with a Co-resident.

At a court hearing, a Defendant is informed of the Charges against him or her, (usually) enters a plea, and a decision is made by a Judge as to the amount of bail, if any. '' 'Mortimer and Isabella were hurried off and arraigned before parliament in November.'
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.
frameExamples: Harry <t>subsisted</t> on ramen and cheap beer through college.
Mortimer and Isabella were hurried off and <t>arraigned</t> before parliament in November.
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
listRoleDefinitions: A person who experiences the effects of some situation or <fen>Condition</fen> for a long period of time.
This role describes the situation that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> must cope with over a long period of time.
A general description of the temporal location of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> while coping with the <fen>Condition</fen>.
Where the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is located when he or she faces the <fen>Condition</fen>.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.
The living organism which requires the <fen>Support</fen> to survive.
The resource that the <fen>Entity</fen> relies on to survive through a situation.
The individual(s) that reside at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The place in which somebody resides.
A person or group of people that the resident is staying with or among.
This role refers to the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Resident</fen> resides.
The <fen>Defendant</fen> is charged with a crime by a <fen>Judge</fen>.
The <fen>Judge</fen> is the head of the court where the arraignment occurs.
<fen>Charges</fen> is the crime with which the <fen>Defendant</fen> is charged.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the arraignment occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arraignment occurs.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where the <fen>Guest</fen> spends a short amount of time.
The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
